t is precisely because the subject triggers such responses, the authors argue, that a volume such as Feminist Nightmares has become a necessity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFeminismxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aFeminismzUnited States. 0aFeminism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aAlcoff, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllan, Tuzyline Jita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaskin, Judith R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChampagne, Rosaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimen, Muriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleischner, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFunk, Nanette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillooly, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, E. Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLooser, Devoney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcClain, Linda C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOstrov Weisser, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatai, Daphne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReid, Robin Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRies, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaddock, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinha, Manisha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel